Do you have a good motivation for this new file besides the imports? The extra imports are all just finiteness to get to `Finset`, and I don't think we should be considering `Finset` as something that's heavy to import. If it is, then we should fix it rather than artificially breaking down downstream files.

I think it doesn't hurt to separate the basics of the algebraic hierarchy from the finiteness hierarchy.
And I don't think the breaking down has to be very artificial.
Okay, but `FreeMonoid` is *literally* `List`, which belongs to the finiteness hierarchy
I've removed the material on 'symbols' from this file -- I will soon make another PR with that material in a separate file, Algebra/FreeMonoid/Symbols.lean
